	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><addressee>Revd. I Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>19 March 1848</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I received your note in the <date>February</date><lb/> Occidents&#44; the <date>March</date> numbers have not yet arrived<lb/> but I have written <persName>Moses</persName> to <sic>prevend</sic> others by Express<lb/> I see no mention if you <sic>intention</sic> of renewing the<lb/> publication&#8212;tho I suppose you <del>have</del> will continue the<lb/> work as before and I have desired <persName>Moses</persName> to forward also<lb/> the <date>April</date> no. by Express&#8212;leaving <placeName>New York</placeName> on <date>Monday</date><lb/> morning  your package need be there on the <date>30th</date> if<lb/> possible.  I have not sent round any list thinking<lb/> it better to continue sending the numbers to the same<lb/> subscribers or some of them might <add>&#63;</add> continue their<lb/> subscriptions&#8212;I know that some will should the<lb/> Occidents come <add>&#63;</add>press of <date>3rd April</date> they will send<lb/> them before my departure and I shall inquire who<lb/> continue to seek others to replace those who withdraw</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am desirous of knowing whether you will<lb/> be at home in the week after <date>Passover</date> wishing to<lb/> secure</p>
			<pb n="2V"/>
				<p>secure your important services for one day of that period<lb/> Should you have any intention of <sic>travelling</sic> will you be so<lb/> good as to let me know.  I have not determined upon<lb/> the day but I believe it will be during the week<lb/> succeeding <date>Passover</date> or rather between the <date>26th April</date> &#38;<lb/> the <date>third of May</date>&#8212;say not later than the <date>third</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I hope my desertion of the Bihelm Maternity will<lb/> not cause you any sorrow perhaps not even surprise<lb/> unto you oblige me by not mentioning this for the present</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">One of the <persName>Mssrs Solomon</persName> was married on <date>Tuesday</date><lb/> to our brightest Gentlemen resident here.  I hope you<lb/> have continued well this winter and enjoyed the<lb/> mildness of the season.  Our winter has only lately<lb/> commenced and yet we have not had sufficient snow<lb/> for the <add>&#63;</add> of the country.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In mentioning the week succeeding the<lb/> termination of <date>passover</date>&#44; I presume it is immaterial<add>&#63;</add> to<lb/> you what day is named between the <date>26th April</date> &#38; <date>3rd May</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I am dear sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">M Joseph<add>&#63;</add></persName></p>
		</body>
